directions: Go through the main entrance and go straight ahead until you get to some stairs leading upstairs. Turn left at these and head through the curtains in front of you. There are also other bathrooms off of the main dining area, but from memory these are gendered.
comment: The owners would prefer if you were a paying customer, but the waiters won't care (or they didn't when I worked there).

I think it's policy to buy something, but they have displayed artwork, and free fruit water most days, and live music or poetry nights! 
There's no rail in the bathroom, I think, but it was pretty spacious, and may be handicap accessible?

name: Campus Center Building at ETSU
comment: There is a ramp and moving chair available to access all parts of this restroom. Additionally, if you have any questions, this building has many safe places for women, LGBTQIA folks, and minorities. The Women's Studies office is a great place to start! Look for SafeZone stickers (pink triangles) outside of office doors.
